# Project Conventions

## Stack

- **Framework:** Astro 5 with React integration (`@astrojs/react`)
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS v4 via `@tailwindcss/vite` plugin
- **Components:** shadcn/ui (new-york style, `components.json` at root)
- **Icons:** Lucide React (`lucide-react`)
- **Package manager:** pnpm (always use `pnpm` â€” never `npm` or `yarn`)

## Package Management

- Install packages: `pnpm add <pkg>`
- Install dev packages: `pnpm add -D <pkg>`
- Add shadcn components: `pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add <component>`
- Run scripts: `pnpm dev`, `pnpm build`, `pnpm preview`

## File Conventions

- Astro pages: `src/pages/`
- Astro layouts: `src/layouts/`
- React components: `src/components/` (`.tsx`)
- shadcn UI components: `src/components/ui/`
- Utilities: `src/lib/`
- Styles: `src/styles/global.css` (imported in `src/layouts/Layout.astro`)

## Import Alias

Use `@/` for all `src/` imports:

```ts
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"
```

## Icons

Use tree-shakeable imports from `lucide-react`:

```tsx
import { ArrowRight, Github } from "lucide-react"
```

Never import the entire library. Always import individual icons by name.
Browse available icons at https://lucide.dev/icons/

## Astro + React

- Use `.astro` files for static/layout content (rendered at build time).
- Use `.tsx` files for interactive components that need client-side hydration.
- Add `client:load`, `client:visible`, or `client:idle` directives when using React components in `.astro` files.

```astro
---
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
---
<Button client:load>Click me</Button>
```
